10 "Crazy" by American country music artist Kenny Rogers was released in December 1984 as the only single from the album What About Me?. The song was Kenny Rogers' eleventh number one country single as a solo artist. The single went to number one for one week and spent a total of thirteen weeks on the country chart.Rogers co-wrote the track with Richard Marx. 

11 "Crazy" by Kenny Rogers is a remake version of Crazy by Willie Nelson.

01 "Crazy" is a ballad composed by Willie Nelson. It has been recorded by several artists, most notably by Patsy Cline, whose version was a #2 country hit in 1962

02 "Crazy" by Patsy Cline is one of her signature songs and the most popular version
